<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="457" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,628,835]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,629,655]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Collett, R." box="[277,435,628,655]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="353 - 357" refId="ref13851" refString="Collett, R. (1898) On some pigeons and parrots from North and Northwest Australia. Proceedings of the General Meetings for Scientific Business of the Zoological Society of London, 1898, 353 - 357. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1898. tb 03152. x" type="journal article" year="1898">Collett (1898)</bibRefCitation>
based the original description on 
<specimenCount box="[816,921,628,655]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" type="adult">two adult</specimenCount>
males collected by Knut Dahl, without specifying any one of them as the 
<typeStatus box="[493,595,664,690]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">holotype</typeStatus>
. One of the specimens was sent to the British Museum (Natural History) (BMNH; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sharpe, R. B." box="[260,405,700,726]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="79 - 515" refId="ref16564" refString="Sharpe, R. B. (1906) 3. Birds. In: The history of the collections contained in the Natural History Departments of the British Museum. Vol. II. Separate historical accounts of the several collections included in the Department of Zoology. Trustees of the British Museum, London, pp. 79 - 515." type="book chapter" year="1906">Sharpe 1906</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Warren, R. L. M." box="[417,567,700,727]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refId="ref16906" refString="Warren, R. L. M. (1966) Type-specimens of birds in the British Museum (Natural History). Vol. 1. Non-Passerines. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 320 pp." type="book" year="1966">Warren 1966</bibRefCitation>
), where it currently is catalogued as NHMUK 1898.10.10.1 (
<bibRefCitation author="Natural History Museum" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refId="ref15696" refString="Natural History Museum (2014 a) Dataset: Collection specimens. Resource: Specimens. Specimen 1898.10. 10.1, Natural History Museum Data Portal (data. nhm. ac. uk). Available from: https: // data. nhm. ac. uk / object / 5995 d 71 a- 6 dc 0 - 4905 - aa 94 - cc 1 ac 3 c 79 cd 5 / 1642550400000 (accessed 14 March 2022)" type="url" year="2014">Natural History Museum 2014a</bibRefCitation>
; Hein van Grouw, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,628,835]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
The original label, written by the collector, is present at the base of the stand (
<figureCitation box="[1087,1200,772,799]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[175,1413,868,1732]" captionTargetId="figure-168@6.[168,1420,858,1738]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Labels of type specimens in the NHMO Bird Collection described by R. Collett. a) Petrophassa rufipennis NHMO- BI-77947 (collector’s label); b) Ptilopus (Leucotreron) alligator NHMO-BI-77948 (collector’s label); c) Psephotus dissimilis NHMO-BI-64125 (collector’s label); d) Psephotus dissimilis NHMO-BI-64125 (NHMO label); e) Psephotus dissimilis NHMO- BI-85843 (collector’s label)." pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Figure 2a</figureCitation>
). The species is here referred to simply as 
<emphasis box="[389,501,808,834]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[393,501,808,834]" class="Aves" family="Columbidae" genus="Columba" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Columba</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
’.
</paragraph>
